@model LIAuppgift.Models.Pages.StartPage

<div class="bg-gray-50 pt-12 pb-10 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
        <div class="lg:text-center flex flex-col rounded-lg shadow-lg bg-white overflow-hidden p-8">            
            <p class="text-3xl leading-8 font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl">
                Welcome!
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-xl text-gray-500 lg:mx-auto">
                Our webshop as all you want, and don't want. At a price that serves us. Nothing is what it seems, and who knows who's watching? Just remember to bring your bitcoin
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col rounded-lg shadow-lg bg-white overflow-hidden mt-10 p-8">
            <dl class="space-y-10 md:space-y-0 md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-x-8 md:gap-y-10">
                <div class="relative">
                    <dt>
                        <div class="absolute flex items-center justify-center h-12 w-12 rounded-md bg-indigo-500 text-white">
                            <!-- Heroicon name: outline/globe-alt -->
                            <svg class="h-6 w-6" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M21 12a9 9 0 01-9 9m9-9a9 9 0 00-9-9m9 9H3m9 9a9 9 0 01-9-9m9 9c1.657 0 3-4.03 3-9s-1.343-9-3-9m0 18c-1.657 0-3-4.03-3-9s1.343-9 3-9m-9 9a9 9 0 019-9" />
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <p class="ml-16 text-lg leading-6 font-medium text-gray-900">All kinds of great and not so great things available from all over the world</p>
                    </dt>
                    <dd class="mt-2 ml-16 text-base text-gray-500">
                        Like surprises? Nothing can compare to the surprise when purchasing stuff from our site. You may or may not get what you order. If not, what could it be? If anything arrives at all. We call that, surprising! All our things are supplied by our "trusted" community and members.
                    </dd>
                </div>

                <div class="relative">
                    <dt>
                        <div class="absolute flex items-center justify-center h-12 w-12 rounded-md bg-indigo-500 text-white">
                            <!-- Heroicon name: outline/scale -->
                            <svg class="h-6 w-6" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 6l3 1m0 0l-3 9a5.002 5.002 0 006.001 0M6 7l3 9M6 7l6-2m6 2l3-1m-3 1l-3 9a5.002 5.002 0 006.001 0M18 7l3 9m-3-9l-6-2m0-2v2m0 16V5m0 16H9m3 0h3" />
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <p class="ml-16 text-lg leading-6 font-medium text-gray-900">50/50 chance your items will arrive</p>
                    </dt>
                    <dd class="mt-2 ml-16 text-base text-gray-500">
                        Basing our delivery logic of Sweden's postal service every transport and delivery is unique. Unique in the way that you never know what will happen. If anything at all. If you get what you order and in time. We strongly recommend buying a lottery ticket at once! (sold separetly)
                    </dd>
                </div>

                <div class="relative">
                    <dt>
                        <div class="absolute flex items-center justify-center h-12 w-12 rounded-md bg-indigo-500 text-white">
                            <!-- Heroicon name: outline/lightning-bolt -->
                            <svg class="h-6 w-6" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z" />
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <p class="ml-16 text-lg leading-6 font-medium text-gray-900">Lightning fast transactions via Bitcoin to our offshore bank accounts</p>
                    </dt>
                    <dd class="mt-2 ml-16 text-base text-gray-500">
                        With our primary exchange unit using Bitcoin we can promise ourselfs secure and fast tax-free income from your purchases. Untraceable and hidden from your local tax ad VAT collectors
                    </dd>
                </div>

                <div class="relative">
                    <dt>
                        <div class="absolute flex items-center justify-center h-12 w-12 rounded-md bg-indigo-500 text-white">
                            <!-- Heroicon name: outline/annotation -->
                            <svg class="h-6 w-6" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 8h10M7 12h4m1 8l-4-4H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h14a2 2 0 012 2v8a2 2 0 01-2 2h-3l-4 4z" />
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <p class="ml-16 text-lg leading-6 font-medium text-gray-900">Full of annoying pop-ups, notifications and more!</p>
                    </dt>
                    <dd class="mt-2 ml-16 text-base text-gray-500">
                        Actually no, but we chosen to have every other site on the web deal with these pop-ups, ads and you-know-what these days. Cookie consent? lol
                    </dd>
                </div>
            </dl>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>